One of the seminars I’m doing on behalf of the 2022 Mr. Olympia at the Olympia University education series is: “Insulin Enhancement and Manipulation for Strength, Performance, and Cognitive Acceleration”. 

I thought I would briefly touch on why my seminars around the world focus on the importance of insulin as it pertains to my work with athletes and celebrities, and work with numerous diabetics referred to me from physicians in numerous countries. 

Through the years various diets come and go, inspired through marketing driven fads or through cherry picked studies and data.

Regardless of the type of diet and focus on macros limited or omitted, activity levels increased through various means, sleep increases/decreases, hormone increases/decreases and imbalances, the impact of any and/or all of the above and the diet utilized is dictated by the impacts to insulin release and insulin receptor sensitivity.

*Insulin determines the efficiency of nutrient delivery, which at the core is the governor to the impact of dietary and physical influence and stimulus. 

Nutrition: 

Macro ingestion individually and through various forms along with macro combination have a direct influence on insulin release, and that release has a direct influence on receptor sensitivity.

*The longer the receptor is exposed to circulating insulin, the less sensitivity to insulin and it’s actions, including a reduction in nutrient delivery.

Hormonal:

Anabolic and Catabolic hormones have a direct influence on insulin release and receptor sensitivity. 

Anabolic hormones tend to increase  receptor sensitivity, increasing the efficiency in the actions of insulin. 

Catabolic hormones tend to be receptor antagonists, reducing the efficiency in the actions of insulin.

Want to learn more?

Join me at the 2022 Mr Olympia for my seminar on Insulin, and additional seminar as part of the TRT/HRT and Supplements roundtable discussion featuring my esteemed colleagues.

Well….after what feels like an eternity, my book is almost done. 

This is by far the most comprehensive book ever written on the the role of insulin and athletic performance. 

I’m doing final editing now, and then it should be ready to roll as I wrap up a few last details in the coming weeks. Sooner hopefully rather than later. 

*I’ll be scheduling a tour for the book release to be part of an interactive seminar, including providing and utilizing the tools referenced in the book to participants. 
This will be a hands on seminar with the book as your interactive guide to the live “science projects” included as part of the seminar. 

More details to come, including links for pre-order of digital and signed hard copies.

Another year completed with nutrition clients at Worlds Strongest Man 2023.
I couldn’t be more proud of my 4 clients reaching the Finals and their relentless hard work. 
Results: 3 of the Top 5: 
Tom Stoltman 2nd (and 4th podium in 4 years) Trey Mitchel 4th (and debut top 5 placing) Evan Singleton 5th (and debut appearance in the finals), Luke Stoltman 8th (and 4th appearance in the finals).
This year was also special supporting Brian Shaw in his final WSM contest from the sole position as a long time friend and fan myself. 🐐 Love ya B 

2023 brings a close to 15 consecutive years with clients in WSM, and 15 consecutive years with clients in the Finals, (with 7 WSM Titles). 
To all my WSM clients past and present~thank you for including me in chasing (and often catching) your dreams, and paving the way inspiring others that come behind you to reach for their dreams. 
The countdown to WSM 2024 starts NOW. 🏆
*thank you to @chadcoy55 @dan_hipkiss @adamderks_strongman for all the amazing teamwork with your training clients, @the_musclemechanic_ ,and thank you to @dr.mcdougle_strongmandoc, @body_whisperer_institute, @indy_musclemike, @brotox_boywonder for the incredible work and collaboration.

It’s been hard to put my thoughts together on your retirement, but here goes…..

A place in history signifies an individual has not only shaped the present but also influenced the course of the future, creating a legacy that will continue to inspire, guide, and resonate with generations to come. 

To Brian, my friend and client for so many years, your achievements transcend the sport, cementing your place in the past, present, and future. 

I’ve had the pleasure of closely watching your journey to champion, husband, father, business owner, promoter, and voice for the voiceless~

Thank you for including me in your journey as you wrote your pages in history. I know there’s so much yet to be written….

Love you brother. 👊🐐
